<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SKIRT PANELS, AERO SIDE SKIRT PANELS, BODY AIR DEFLECTORS,
        BUMPERS AND ROOFS - 0. CAB SKIRT PANELS - REMOVE CAB SKIRT PANELS 9200i, 9400i and 9900i (LONG DESIGN)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>REMOVE CAB SKIRT PANELS 9200
            <emph type="italic">i</emph>, 9400
            <emph type="italic">i</emph>
            and 9900
            <emph type="italic">i</emph>
            (LONG DESIGN)
        </title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The cab skirts have 3 or 4 panel (sections) depending on the vehicle model. Each panel (section) can
                be removed separately. To remove street side skirt panels, begin at the rear panel and move forward. To
                remove curb side panels, begin at front and move toward rear.
            </para>
            <para>The following procedures are for removing all panels (sections) and the panel support frames either
                separately or as a complete assembly.
            </para>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove screws securing upper and lower aluminum step plates and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1602401">anti-rattle insulator
                            <xref refid="f1602401"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        from the lower step plate.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1602402">Remove one xmas tree fastener
                            <xref refid="f1602402"/>
                        </hotlnk>
                        from the skirt tie; this will separate the panels. It does not matter which fastener is removed.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove skirt panels.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <figure id="f1602401" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1602401" filename="../figg16/g1602401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="168px" resolution="72" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Anti -Rattle Insulator</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RUBBER PAD (FACING OUTWARD)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1602402" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1602402" filename="../figg16/g1602402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="208px" resolution="72" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Xmas Tree Fastener</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. XMAS TREE FASTENER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SKIRT TIE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SKIRT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SKIRT EXTENSION (RUBBER)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal Skirt Panel(s) With Frame Assembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws from retaining step plates at second panel from front.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove step plate and insulator
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602401">
                        <xref refid="f1602401"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    , then remove skirt panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602403">Remove fuel tank strap "J" bolt from skirt frame
                        <xref refid="f1602403"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602403" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1602403" filename="../figg16/g1602403.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="532px"
                         scalefitheight="472px" resolution="72" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Skirt Frame Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FUEL TANK STRAP CONNECTION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SKIRT FRAME TO CHASSIS FRAME LOCK PIN LOCATION</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SKIRT FRAME ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. STEP FRAME MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lock and pin securing skirt frame to vehicle frame (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602403">Item 2)
                        <xref refid="f1602403"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block each end of the skirt frame
                    <emph type="bold">(use suitable stands or wood blocks)</emph>. Do not put pressure on the skirt
                    frame assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602404">Remove nuts/bolts securing front skirt frame to vehicle frame (Item 1)
                        <xref refid="f1602404"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602404" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1602404" filename="../figg16/g1602404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Frame Bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BOLT/NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRAME BRACKET (SKIRT)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FRAME (SKIRT)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602405">Remove nuts/bolts (Item 1) securing rear skirt frame
                        <xref refid="f1602405"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    to the vehicle frame. Before removing nuts/bolts,
                    <emph type="bold">have an assistant help remove skirt frame assembly.</emph>
                    Remove frame stands with assistant, and pull skirt frame assembly from vehicle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602405" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1602405" filename="../figg16/g1602405.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="248px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Frame Skirt</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BOLT/NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRAME (SKIRT)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
